						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the Kuraṅganātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year [3.]</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the reign of Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsarivarman. The date portion is damaged. Only 3 is visible.</p>						

						<p>This records a sale of land to [Tirukkurakkuttuṟai]p-Perumāṉaḍigaḷ for 2 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju.</hi> The portion containing the other details is damaged. This also records another endowment of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> for a day lamp to god Perumāṉaḍigaḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
